When synchronizing my project in eclipse 3.2 with cvs I get the following message: 
cvs server: nothing known about: package/Myclass.java

Synchronizing in Eclipse 3.2 does work properly, but there might be some problems with the cvs server you are connecting to. Have you tried connecting to any other servers (such as dev.eclipse.org)?

Did you set up the cvs server? Is there any way for us to connect (read only) to the server to test this out?

It would also be helpful if you follwed the steps at this URL to get a trace of
what Eclipse is sending to the server and what the server is sending back. This
may help identify the problem.

http://wiki.eclipse.org/index.php/CVS_FAQ#Is_there_any_equivalent_to_CVS_CLIENT_LOG_is_Eclipse.3F

Please reopen with requested information if you are still having problems.

I didn't set up the cvs server (cvsnt) but it works fine with eclipse 3.1
You cannot connect to the server.

What version of CVSNT are you using?

I have tried to reproduce the failure but have not been able to. Does the file "core/workflow/duedate/DuedateHelper.java" exist in the repository? Also, the trace you have provided is not complete (i.e. it only contains the end due to the buffer size of your DOS console). Could you either increase the buffer size (using the dorpdown menu in the upeer left of the title bar to access the Properties dialog) or try synchronizing the file that fails by itself.

It would also be helpful to know if the server is properly configured to work with Eclipse as described in the following URL:

http://wiki.eclipse.org/index.php/CVS_FAQ#How_do_I_configure_CVSNT_to_work_with_Eclipse.3F

Does the server have the appropriate settings? Are there any other customized settings?

I have not been able to reproduce this failure with stated version of CVSNT and the latest 3.2.1 maintenance builds. If you are still experiencing this problem, please reopen with the requested information.
